text.tspan: LESSONS
LEARNED REPORT
0 DECEMBER 202
Name:
Handwritten Recognition
System
Project Sponsor:
Dato Sri Idzhan Khalid Bin Abu Bakar
Project Manager:
Lai Kah Heng
Project Dates:
Final Budget:
a.
Did the project meet scope, time and cost goals?
Yes, the project meets both the project and product scopes as discussed in the
proposal. We also manage to get the project done within the given time and
budget.
b.
What was the
success criteria listed in the project scope statement?
The project is considered successful if we meet both the project and product
scopes. The following success criteria are listed in the project scope:
i)
The project scope for this project is the
set
of
requirements for developing the
project, which must consist of Neural Network and Python programming
domains.
ii) The product scope includes the ability to finish a handwritten recognition
system that is able to detect the characters or words successful
ly and accurately.
iii) No additional cost or budget is needed for the project.
c.
Reflect on whether or not you met the project success criteria.
Since none of us are experts in Neural Network and Python programming, it will
at least take a month to learn
and become familiar with the domain. We are
aware that taking the course may jeopardise our ability to complete the project
on time. However, we are able to complete the Neural Network and Python
programming course on time. The only thing we were bothered
by was that we
were rushing to finish the course and start the project.
We completed the system
exactly as planned during the planning stage. Fortunately, we have won the
customer’s satisfaction. Besides, the project was able to be completed within the
est
imated time and budget.
d.
What were the main lessons your team learned from this project?
The most important lesson
our team learned from this project is how teamwork
plays the most important role in ensuring that the project deliverables, scope,
and goals
are achieved. Next, communication is the key to making sure that the
project is progressing in the right direction. If the team is unresponsive and not
discussing things together, it can ruin the final product or the project might fail
We also learned th
at the Gantt chart is the essential document for the team
members to follow so that the project can be completed within the estimated time
in order to fulfil the project’s scope.
